        "content": "\ud83c\udfad Debate Phase: Rebuttals\n\ud83d\udccc Your Position: Social media is a net positive\n\ud83d\udcca Your Progress: 1 arguments, 0 rebuttals\n\ud83d\udcc8 Completion: 100%\n\n\ud83d\udcdd Instructions: Respond to your opponent's arguments. Point out flaws, contradictions, or weaknesses. Defend your own position against their attacks.\n\n\ud83d\udc65 Opponent Arguments:\nDigitalWellbeing (Social media needs mental health reforms):\n  1. DigitalWellbeing: Social media needs mental health reforms\n\nSocial media platforms often prioritize engagement and profit over user well-being, leading to addictive usage patterns, cyberbullying, and \nPrivacyAdvocate (Social media violates privacy rights):\n  1. Social media companies routinely collect vast amounts of personal data beyond what is necessary for their services, often without explicit user consent or awareness. They use sophisticated algorithms ",
